SYNOPSIS
        varargs int visible_to(object oItem, object oObserver, object oEnv)

DESCRIPTION
	Returns 1 if '<oItem>' is visible to '<oObserver>' in optional
	environment '<oEnv>'. If '<oEnv>' is not suppled, it defaults to the
	environment of '<oItem>'.

	This function performs all standard checks including 'query_invis'
	checks modified by the 'see_invis' attribute, 'query_inventory_hidden'
	checks, and finally spectrum checks.

	NOTE: It does not check whether '<oObserver>' and '<oItem>' are actually
	      in the same environment or even have access to each other's
	      environments in any way.

EXAMPLE
	// This first example will take an object 'sword' that is laying on the
	// ground and if not visible to the player, tell them so.
	object oObj;

	oObj = present("sword", environment(this_player()));
	if (!visible_to(oObj, this_player()))
	  write("You see no sword here!\n");

